The paper deals with tensor decomposition methods for convolutional neural networks, which are primarily used in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves neural architecture search, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and nonlinear activations, which are relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
